<subSubSection id="46364F8BCE54F62BC570BFF6AE52DF30" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AA447E2769158C16827425CDF7FB5A49" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FBECF6F25A06DF2BF94AB3DDF7FB1CAF" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">
2.7 mm (n = 1), 2.7 
<normalizedToken id="7065537FF1FFEDAD645CBEF271F561EF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the elytral apex strongly acuminate, declivital interstriae unarmed along its entire length, antennal club with two sutures on posterior face, elytral discal interstriae impunctate, declivity nearly devoid of granules except for interstriae 1 and 3 on acuminate projection, and declivity with a carina extending from apex to interstriae 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
